WEBVTT

00:00.098 --> 00:01.019
Good to see you.

00:02.160 --> 00:03.342
All right, yeah.

00:04.523 --> 00:06.025
What a good morning so far.

00:07.046 --> 00:10.971
We are in this series called Stepping into the Story.

00:10.991 --> 00:23.826
And how wonderful to just have heard all the different individuals, Pete, Nikki, James that have brought some really encouraging words.

00:23.970 --> 00:30.057
I just want to say thank you always to Pete and Nikki for this opportunity, and it's always a joy to share.

00:30.978 --> 00:40.969
I don't know if you found yourself ever in a situation where you thought, I've said yes to something, and now I'm wondering, what am I doing?

00:41.009 --> 00:49.458
The anxiety is there, the fear is there, the intrepidation, and you think, was I really hearing correctly?

00:49.730 --> 00:55.596
And for us recently, we found ourselves no less in the French Alps.

00:56.237 --> 00:59.641
And I'll never forget when I heard the click, click sound.

00:59.781 --> 01:01.283
Dave, you'll know what I'm talking about.

01:01.683 --> 01:04.146
You're putting on those snow skis.

01:04.686 --> 01:12.115
And just like two weeks ago, our son had said for my 30th birthday, we would love to go skiing.

01:12.635 --> 01:15.218
Now, before you think, are you crazy?

01:15.362 --> 01:17.905
We had grown up skiing.

01:17.925 --> 01:23.011
I did as a child and then we took our kids year after year.

01:23.091 --> 01:25.174
That was our one vacation that we did.

01:25.714 --> 01:30.880
And do you know, for the most part, started going down that hill and I was like, yeah, I got this.

01:31.000 --> 01:31.861
This is good.

01:32.022 --> 01:33.343
We're doing okay.

01:33.944 --> 01:39.510
I had to block out the fact that everyone around me was like in their 20s looking like you guys.

01:39.671 --> 01:42.514
And I was like, okay, we can do this.

01:42.754 --> 01:47.359
And, you know, remarkably, the entire week we stayed safe.

01:47.900 --> 02:00.073
And it's funny because that phrase, Claire Parker, dear friend before I went, said, just want to say one thing, two words, stay safe.

02:00.654 --> 02:06.760
And over and over, the Holy Spirit would use that, you know, like, okay, don't you're getting a little fast here?

02:06.860 --> 02:10.224
And, you know, but the Lord was good.

02:10.264 --> 02:11.986
We came back in one piece.

02:12.418 --> 02:15.641
There was, however, and we had glorious weather.

02:15.681 --> 02:23.689
I'm sorry it rained here, because it was incredible just seeing the mountains and the majesty of the Lord.

02:23.769 --> 02:25.471
And it made me think of that scripture.

02:25.511 --> 02:27.933
I lift my eyes to the hills.

02:28.013 --> 02:29.595
Where does my help come from?

02:30.135 --> 02:33.258
My help comes from the Lord, the maker of heaven and earth.

02:33.318 --> 02:39.524
And even in the gondola, it was just our family, but we started worshiping and praising.

02:39.704 --> 02:41.426
And it was a powerful moment.

02:41.826 --> 02:49.896
And towards the end of the week, though, we realized, oh, our legs are getting a little tired, and our families have skied with Dave and Don.

02:49.916 --> 02:51.198
That's why I keep looking at him.

02:51.738 --> 02:55.283
But our legs were tired, and we started getting sloppy.

02:55.863 --> 02:57.165
Wouldn't you agree?

02:57.185 --> 02:57.886
Yeah.

02:57.906 --> 03:04.294
So what we should have done at the beginning of the week is had a lesson, but leave it to us.

03:04.434 --> 03:05.716
We're fine.

03:06.076 --> 03:10.802
So we had a lesson on the very last day.

03:11.234 --> 03:19.308
And it was quite funny because I meet this instructor and he's, first of all, I think his eyes, he saw my retro jumpsuit.

03:19.369 --> 03:21.993
It's like 30 years old and he's like, oh, okay.

03:22.594 --> 03:33.374
And then for some reason, I just happened to say, by the way, and I told him our ages, at this point, his eyes got really big and like, shouldn't you be in the spa?

03:33.955 --> 03:35.858
Like, why are you here?

03:36.290 --> 03:40.977
And it was like, well, our goal is we want to stay safe, keep fit.

03:41.118 --> 03:47.127
We haven't skied in about 12 years, and this instructor is looking really panicked.

03:47.868 --> 03:50.573
But he said, OK, what's your goal?

03:50.813 --> 03:55.060
And I said, well, I just want to be able to ski with all of my grandkids one day.

03:55.080 --> 03:58.866
I could just play in this snow, but yeah, let's ski.

03:59.146 --> 04:01.690
So he takes us out, and we're doing pretty good.

04:02.632 --> 04:03.954
It is the last day.

04:04.034 --> 04:06.978
And we come on this little pass.

04:07.018 --> 04:12.805
And when I say a pass, it's not even a path as big as the width of the row.

04:12.825 --> 04:15.368
A lot of people are on this pass.

04:15.388 --> 04:20.534
So the instructor, for some reason, just wants to make sure we're okay, and he stops.

04:21.615 --> 04:24.959
I'm the one right behind him, so I'm like, and I stop.

04:26.281 --> 04:33.970
The next thing that happens, I felt this weight beyond like a rugby tackle.

04:34.434 --> 04:35.015
Boom.

04:35.075 --> 04:38.581
And the next thing I know, I am on the ground.

04:38.701 --> 04:40.825
My hip hits the hard eyes.

04:41.446 --> 04:42.948
And I see these skis.

04:43.048 --> 04:47.776
And the first thing I think is at my age, this could be a good lawsuit.

04:50.321 --> 04:55.229
But then I turn around and I see my dear beloved.

04:57.152 --> 05:00.818
My dear beloved has knocked me flat on my backside.

05:01.058 --> 05:08.168
Skis came off and all I thought was, I had not even fallen all week and you took me out.

05:08.308 --> 05:11.753
I love you still there.

05:11.773 --> 05:18.742
And it was at that moment, he goes, babe, I'm so sorry, I couldn't stop.

05:18.882 --> 05:19.844
And I'm like, you think?

05:20.885 --> 05:27.474
Yeah, but at that moment, I just had to let grace fill my heart.

05:27.842 --> 05:30.585
I was like, okay, everything, I feel like I'm okay.

05:30.666 --> 05:32.027
Yep, we're all in one piece.

05:33.129 --> 05:37.574
Let grace fill my heart and just say, okay, come on, let's go.

05:37.594 --> 05:42.180
And this is a story I'd love to actually share with you.

05:42.200 --> 05:53.394
Today, we're looking at a woman who took those steps that changed the trajectory of generations.

05:53.730 --> 06:03.324
We're looking at a story of a woman who foreshadows the inclusion of all nations, all people in God's redemptive plan.

06:04.046 --> 06:07.671
It's a story of a woman who heard of God's deliverance.

06:07.751 --> 06:16.224
In fact, many had heard that she was the only one who believed and God used her right where she was.

06:18.607 --> 06:22.994
In this belief, she was gripped by God's grace.

06:23.842 --> 06:27.868
And so today I want us to look at gripped by grace.

06:28.489 --> 06:33.477
There's three points I'm gonna have you quickly tell them to the person sitting next to you, all right?

06:33.918 --> 06:37.203
So here's the first one, grace found her.

06:37.263 --> 06:39.306
Turn to your neighbor and say that.

06:40.708 --> 06:42.351
Grace found her.

06:42.411 --> 06:46.818
One more time, grace found her, okay?

06:47.379 --> 06:48.320
All right, you got it.

06:48.661 --> 06:51.986
The second thing is that grace

06:52.354 --> 06:53.996
stirred her heart.

06:55.058 --> 06:57.621
Tell your neighbor, Grace stirred her heart.

06:58.742 --> 07:03.028
So Grace found her, Grace stirred her heart.

07:03.048 --> 07:08.355
The third one is Grace reclaimed her and her household.

07:09.737 --> 07:13.502
Amen.

07:13.762 --> 07:20.050
And today we are looking at the story of Rahab, that

07:20.546 --> 07:24.270
prophetic word rage that you gave couldn't have been more spot on.

07:24.391 --> 07:28.375
So I love the way God has something stirring in our hearts.

07:29.096 --> 07:31.959
So here we are, the story of Rahab.

07:32.260 --> 07:34.723
Give us a hand if you know the story of Rahab.

07:35.704 --> 07:44.434
I love it because as I've studied and unpacked that, even this morning, he was showing me things that I had missed.

07:44.738 --> 07:52.992
And so the wonderful thing at looking at Scripture and back on the lives of those who said, yes, is we could learn from them.

07:53.012 --> 08:00.063
We can embrace, think about what they had to choose and see what Holy Spirit has for you.

08:00.544 --> 08:04.010
So I pray that each of us would take at least one thing.

08:04.050 --> 08:11.602
You'd be gripped by grace when he finds you, stirs your heart and reclaims you.

08:11.810 --> 08:15.795
So here we are in Joshua 2, verse 1, and it says this.

08:17.698 --> 08:23.266
Now Joshua, the son of none sent out two men from Shaitan.

08:23.606 --> 08:24.507
I'll call it that.

08:26.009 --> 08:26.570
There you go.

08:27.211 --> 08:31.657
Believe it or not, it's actually pronounced the way you're thinking, but I'm not going to do that from up here.

08:33.099 --> 08:41.330
It actually means a cage to grove to spy secretly, saying go view the land, especially Jericho.

08:41.538 --> 08:45.824
So they came to the house of a harlot named Rahab and lodged there.

08:46.484 --> 08:52.813
And what we want to take out from this, when a Joshua sent two men, he learned from the past.

08:52.933 --> 08:54.675
Moses sent how many men?

08:55.816 --> 08:57.579
Yeah, he sent 12 spies.

08:58.460 --> 09:00.222
Didn't go down very well.

09:00.362 --> 09:01.844
Ten of them were negative.

09:02.185 --> 09:06.030
They ended up hanging out in the desert for 40 more years.

09:06.590 --> 09:09.394
So he learned from past leadership.

09:09.634 --> 09:13.839
He said, two spies secretly, and they have this reconnaissance mission.

09:14.259 --> 09:17.202
And the first thing they do is come to Jericho.

09:17.723 --> 09:27.033
Jericho, this fortified city, it was surrounded by strong springs like an oasis.

09:27.814 --> 09:31.698
And it was a place where many, many people were.

09:31.738 --> 09:39.346
And the thing that I wanted us to grasp is the very first thing sometimes when we say yes to God,

09:39.490 --> 09:42.494
And here they are, they're spying out the land.

09:42.534 --> 09:45.177
They know that they're meant to take the land.

09:45.898 --> 09:50.163
The first thing they do is run into this massive obstacle.

09:51.044 --> 09:58.153
Any of you feel like that when you said, yes, you stepped in and all of a sudden you're like, oh, I wasn't expecting that.

09:58.534 --> 09:59.575
You're stretched.

10:00.256 --> 10:05.042
And what I thought the Holy Spirit was saying in this moment from Scripture,

10:05.218 --> 10:10.123
One of the powerful things is to align our mind with truth.

10:10.964 --> 10:16.249
Second Corinthians 12-9, Paul has this encounter with Jesus.

10:16.369 --> 10:17.890
And Jesus says, what?

10:18.571 --> 10:21.734
My grace is sufficient.

10:22.395 --> 10:29.061
My grace is sufficient for my power is made perfect in your weakness.

10:30.102 --> 10:34.066
So when we are weak, his strength infuses us,

10:34.210 --> 10:41.862
1 Thessalonians 524 says, faithful is he who calls you and he will do it.

10:43.124 --> 10:47.851
He is faithful and he will do it when he asks you to step into something.

10:48.552 --> 10:55.743
And over and over, what you see is that they will face, this is the first of many obstacles.

10:55.864 --> 11:02.514
If you look over in Joshua 12, king after king after king after king is listed,

11:02.818 --> 11:06.882
as those that Joshua and the people of Israel defeated.

11:07.503 --> 11:09.004
So it's the first of many.

11:11.827 --> 11:21.916
To understand the story of Jericho falling, it could only be looked at in the light and context of the history and redemption of God.

11:22.577 --> 11:28.363
I want you to imagine for over 400 years the Canaanites had settled in this land.

11:29.043 --> 11:31.826
And here it was a culture that was steeped

11:32.066 --> 11:36.191
and idolatry, pagan worship, and false gods.

11:36.632 --> 11:42.880
So generation after generation, they rejected the true God of Israel.

11:43.741 --> 11:52.913
And here, that promise, that Abrahamic covenant that was set in Genesis, it is about to take place.

11:53.033 --> 11:55.016
It is the beginning of part of it.

11:55.637 --> 11:56.938
So that's Jericho.

11:57.119 --> 11:59.762
I loved that we were singing today.

11:59.938 --> 12:04.243
that our praise is the shout that brings Jericho down.

12:04.303 --> 12:11.553
There are some Jericho walls in our own life that only by refocusing and praising and going, God, you're good.

12:11.953 --> 12:13.114
God, I don't see it.

12:13.255 --> 12:14.676
God, I don't understand.

12:14.777 --> 12:15.538
I don't get it.

12:16.419 --> 12:23.107
But as you praise, He gets so much of our life, our perspective.

12:23.648 --> 12:25.170
And He says, keep praising.

12:25.250 --> 12:28.754
That shout will bring that wall down.

12:30.306 --> 12:31.447
Rahab's house.

12:32.328 --> 12:38.715
It was an inn, a perfect place to stay for people coming in and out of the city.

12:39.115 --> 12:49.506
If you were a foreigner coming in, then it wouldn't be that it was not that big of a deal because they were used to people coming in and out.

12:52.549 --> 12:57.714
The second thing that we want to look at

12:58.210 --> 13:01.633
is right here, Grace found her.

13:02.314 --> 13:03.795
Grace found Rahab.

13:04.496 --> 13:05.137
I love this.

13:05.697 --> 13:10.061
God providentially sent the spies to her in his sovereignty.

13:10.942 --> 13:22.894
He led the spies to the one person and all of Canaan, that, and all of Jericho, that believed in him.

13:22.954 --> 13:27.378
And you have to understand, with Rahab,

13:27.810 --> 13:32.296
She didn't grow up, she didn't get faith from her parents.

13:33.077 --> 13:34.599
There was pagan worship.

13:35.079 --> 13:41.267
She didn't have prophets going up and down the streets, you know, saying, repent, turn to God.

13:41.707 --> 13:46.373
She wouldn't have heard, she would not have heard the law and the teaching.

13:47.034 --> 13:53.362
She would not have engaged in the festivals that would help her understand who Jehovah God was.

13:54.242 --> 14:02.755
But yet, the only thing we know about her is that she heard of the victories of God.

14:03.276 --> 14:09.165
And with that little thing, she believed, which is so powerful.

14:10.587 --> 14:15.494
There's so much here, but for a lot of us, here we are.

14:15.534 --> 14:19.280
We hear week after week.

14:20.241 --> 14:23.346
And some of us believe that no

14:23.746 --> 14:25.308
I've got to get things together.

14:25.348 --> 14:34.421
I've got to present this image of myself where I don't have enough Bible knowledge to go and go into the schools like Big Love is and teaching.

14:34.882 --> 14:39.528
And all he's saying, my little becomes much.

14:42.252 --> 14:43.734
My little becomes much.

14:45.216 --> 14:52.146
So Grace finds her and I love that even though she lived in a godless culture,

14:52.418 --> 14:55.923
She heard the stories of Israel's powerful God.

14:57.265 --> 15:00.049
So some commentaries say she was an innkeeper.

15:00.389 --> 15:01.150
Let's face it.

15:01.210 --> 15:02.492
She was a prostitute.

15:03.053 --> 15:04.074
That's what she did.

15:04.094 --> 15:05.837
That she was a businesswoman.

15:05.897 --> 15:06.838
She was smart.

15:07.539 --> 15:11.424
She was very quick on her feet and we'll see here.

15:12.446 --> 15:13.467
So what happens?

15:13.507 --> 15:14.709
Let me read the scripture.

15:14.749 --> 15:21.138
She has this conversation with

15:21.890 --> 15:23.092
with the spies.

15:23.192 --> 15:25.756
So let me just give you a quick summary.

15:27.579 --> 15:33.007
Rahab believes in the God of Israel, just a little seed that stirs her heart.

15:35.250 --> 15:41.319
The spies come to her house and the scripture says that she peacefully let them in.

15:41.459 --> 15:43.442
She peacefully welcomes them.

15:44.003 --> 15:51.154
And what ensues is that immediately word gets out to the king and the king says to Rahab,

15:51.714 --> 15:53.236
bring the spies to me."

15:53.256 --> 15:59.422
Now, what I noticed when I studied this, he did not ask, are the spies in your house?

16:00.163 --> 16:01.725
He said, bring them to me.

16:01.745 --> 16:09.313
And the first thing we see of Rahab in this place gripped by grace, she is courageous.

16:09.914 --> 16:21.586
The king summons and says, bring them and in resolving to like a higher authority that she's now believing, she says, they're not here.

16:22.114 --> 16:27.322
The king's messengers come and they say, are the guys here?

16:27.363 --> 16:34.875
And she says they were here, but now they've gone away and sends them away from the spies.

16:35.356 --> 16:38.781
So here she's a woman of influence.

16:38.801 --> 16:45.212
Now I don't know if I was watching a movie and I see some guards rushing to a house, what do you expect them to do?

16:45.252 --> 16:49.138
Search the house, right?

16:49.826 --> 16:52.309
They take Rahab at her word.

16:52.410 --> 16:53.711
She says, they're not here.

16:53.731 --> 16:55.834
And they say, okay.

16:56.455 --> 17:11.456
Now what that tells us, she's a woman of influence, but also in that society, in a Canaanite society, actually believing a prostitute had high regard.

17:12.537 --> 17:18.706
And because many were priestess in their temples, in their worship.

17:19.074 --> 17:32.689
So she used her influence where before she had used it to serve false gods at this moment, she's surrendering her heart to God and saying, no, they're not here.

17:32.930 --> 17:38.155
And he uses her in a different way as she is.

17:38.176 --> 17:40.438
I find that remarkable.

17:41.079 --> 17:42.500
She didn't clean up her act.

17:42.520 --> 17:45.824
She didn't get rid of her business right there.

17:46.345 --> 17:47.506
God used her.

17:48.194 --> 17:49.296
And that's a word.

17:49.336 --> 17:50.557
That's a word for me.

17:50.577 --> 17:52.100
That's a word for each of us.

17:53.001 --> 17:54.202
Right where you are.

17:54.923 --> 17:55.925
God will use you.

17:56.906 --> 17:58.989
Turn to your neighbor and say that.

17:59.169 --> 18:00.111
Right where you are.

18:03.235 --> 18:04.477
God will use you.

18:04.497 --> 18:06.960
Amen, amen.

18:08.723 --> 18:10.365
His grace found her.

18:10.425 --> 18:13.850
He uses her as she is.

18:14.651 --> 18:16.594
Right where he finds her.

18:17.186 --> 18:18.988
for his glory.

18:20.990 --> 18:24.053
Can I just ask, who were we to limit God?

18:28.778 --> 18:30.921
Yeah, God stirred her heart.

18:33.403 --> 18:34.785
God stirred her heart.

18:35.065 --> 18:40.351
And in this scripture, let me just explain, she has this conversation.

18:40.371 --> 18:46.898
So she hides the spies on the roof.

18:47.042 --> 18:51.768
King's men go, and she goes up to the roof, and she has this conversation.

18:52.189 --> 18:53.630
And let me read this together.

18:53.650 --> 19:01.020
And this is actually called, so it's Joshua 2, verses 9 and 11, and it's called Rahab's Confession.

19:01.621 --> 19:04.665
I know the Lord has given you this land, she told them.

19:05.165 --> 19:06.727
We are all afraid of you.

19:06.767 --> 19:12.114
Everyone in the land is living in terror.

19:12.642 --> 19:19.431
For we have heard how the Lord made a dry path for you through the Red Sea when you left Egypt.

19:20.052 --> 19:23.336
No wonder our hearts have melted in fear.

19:24.037 --> 19:27.562
No one has the courage to fight after hearing such things.

19:28.163 --> 19:35.072
For the Lord's your God is the supreme God of heavens above and on the earth.

19:36.154 --> 19:40.359
So we see that grace stirred her heart.

19:41.000 --> 19:42.482
She had heard

19:42.626 --> 19:47.531
of the victories of the God of Israel.

19:49.574 --> 19:52.717
Do we allow the Holy Spirit to stir our hearts?

19:53.778 --> 19:59.524
Or if we harden our hearts, have we put walls like a Jericho?

19:59.564 --> 20:04.530
I had a picture of that that sometimes we create these safe walls around us.

20:05.911 --> 20:12.178
It's easy to come, hear a talk, do a bit of worship, leave, and that's it.

20:12.802 --> 20:16.807
And I feel like today he's saying, let these walls come down.

20:16.867 --> 20:24.836
There's so many people that are ready to hear, ready to receive his truth.

20:25.717 --> 20:31.203
And I love because Rahab recognized God's power, not Israel's.

20:32.585 --> 20:34.647
She didn't commend the army.

20:34.687 --> 20:37.250
She gave the true source.

20:37.350 --> 20:40.754
She commended God, his power.

20:41.090 --> 20:45.814
And it was at this pivotal moment that she chooses to act.

20:48.277 --> 20:49.878
I hope that resonates with you.

20:50.839 --> 20:56.064
It's a choice at that key, key moment to act.

20:56.645 --> 21:02.610
And God's grace meets her there when he uses her to bring the spies to safety.

21:02.650 --> 21:10.898
As I was thinking about this, I was reminded of just a little incident I had with one of my granddaughters

21:10.978 --> 21:20.751
I was up there watching one of our granddaughters Gabriella and we were having fun and playing and I just gave her the biggest hug and said, I love you so much.

21:21.752 --> 21:27.680
And she hugged me back and said, I'm glad you're having a good day with me.

21:27.720 --> 21:35.250
Now I thought she of course would say, I love you too.

21:35.330 --> 21:36.431
I was so precious.

21:36.511 --> 21:38.293
I was like, I have to go write that down.

21:38.713 --> 21:41.256
I'm glad you're having such a good day with me.

21:41.296 --> 21:50.185
And as the Holy Spirit brought that to mind, it was like the Lord said, that is an example of delight.

21:51.606 --> 21:53.308
Delight yourself and the Lord.

21:53.769 --> 21:55.410
He delights in you.

21:55.450 --> 22:03.218
And he wants us to delight in him in his presence, having that time together.

22:03.842 --> 22:10.070
Do you know when I'm trying to figure out what to speak on just for since last time I spoke?

22:10.230 --> 22:12.833
I'm just writing in my journal, Lord, what are you saying?

22:12.953 --> 22:13.734
What are you hearing?

22:13.774 --> 22:15.477
What do you want me to hear?

22:15.517 --> 22:18.781
And it's that communion, that delight.

22:19.922 --> 22:20.783
And I love this.

22:21.324 --> 22:23.587
Raise your hand if you've heard of Charles Spurgeon.

22:23.627 --> 22:25.429
